30/01/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Members of the Special Police arrested some 50 alleged members of the al-Qaeda terrorist network, in simultaneous raids conducted Monday (January 29th) in the cities of Konya, Istanbul, Izmir, Kocaeli and Mardin. Media reports suggest the police had the suspects under surveillance for about 18 months. Two deadly bombings in Istanbul in November 2003 are blamed on al-Qaeda. (Aksam, Hurriyet - 30/01/07; Anadolu Agency, NTV - 29/01/07)
